It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that has only been minimally decorated.
Take down the ugly electric fireplace and stove. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom order a wardrobe.
We usually start by drawing a rough pencil sketch...
The chaotic phase has passed.
A few dead birds were found behind the flue, their bodies completely dried up :(
Get ready for the plasterers next week.
Very satisfied with the small niche next to it.
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet 😈)
Ha ha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Do you remember the addition of the cute little vents to prevent the chimney from getting damp?
Sweep has installed both the chimney cap and the chimney cover. The white-shouldered starlings that like to nest in chimneys should now be safer in the future. 🪺
The plasterer has finished. We will lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork mat has already been laid down, and a roll of toilet paper was used as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready for installation. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break first.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because we needed to make cuts around the door frame to ensure a seamless connection with the corridor (which is also being laid with flooring), and the operation was quite tedious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me.
Finally, it's done, but it's all messed up! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Tonight, I can finally sleep well!
The corridor floor and baseboards are still not done. The renovation workers didn't come for a month, so we can only manage to live here now, with nothing but bare drywall in the room.
In the evening, do a simple DIY job: use a dovetail saw and chisel to cut off part of the bottom of the door frame, so the floor can fit perfectly underneath.
The felt lining on the corridor is also laid out.
We finished laying the floor in the corridor yesterday! This morning, I got up at 5 a.m. to go to Heathrow Airport, picked up the first package, had a nap, and now finally can start installing baseboards in the corridor. We'll do the grouting after the adhesive dries.
